properties.name: Beatroot Veggie Cafe
properties.description: Posted by Joedonnachie Beatroot is my favourite place to eat. It\'s cheap, it\'s cheerful, and it serves the best organic, vegetarian food in London. I\'ve introduced quite a few of my friends to this place and they\'ve all been very positive about it.

properties.name: Benjamin Franklin House
properties.description: Posted by Joedonnachie36 Craven Street, London, WC2N 5NFBenjamin Franklin, founding father of the United States and the original personal development expert, lived at this house for about 16 years. That was during his second stay in London. On his first visit to London he was a young man of eighteen. It was during that earlier visit that he swam the river Thames from Chelsea to Blackfriars Bridge.

properties.name: Circus Space
properties.description: Posted by Joedonnachie Britian\'s leading school of contemporary circus, Circus Space offers degree courses in circus and a range of adult day and evening classes in circus skills such as static and flying trapeze, tightwire, acrobalance and tumbling

properties.name: Corde Lisse Classes at Brixton St Vincents
properties.description: Posted by JoedonnachieBrixton St Vincents Community Centre is an arts orientated community centre providing a base for local groups and which hires space for rehearsals, workshops, evening classes, children’s parties and meetings. One of those evening classes is Catrin Osborne\'s corde lisse class which runs on a Wednesday evening. Read all about it at the link provided.

properties.name: The Hangar, Aerial and Acrobatic Circus Skills Training
properties.description: Posted by Joedonnachie The Hangar is in an old industrial unit in Marshgate Lane in East London. That\'s near Stratford by the way. Pudding Mill Lane, the nearest station, is on the Docklands Light Railway. They have all sorts of circus type evening courses at the Hangar. Silks and trapeze and acrobalance for starters. The instructors are professional performers and the standard of teaching is excellent.

properties.name: Vitaorganic, Vegetarian Restaurant
properties.description: Posted by Joedonnachie I can\'t decide whether Vitaorganic or Beatroot is my favourite vegetarian eating place in Soho. I\'ll have to keep going back to each until I make up my mind
